[49m[38;5;9m- 13    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon SQS for the message queue.** Messages awaiting timing decisions sit in SQS with visibility timeouts aligned to their delivery windows. SQS handles the durability, ordering, and retry semantics. Dead letter queues catch messages that fail to schedule.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon SQS for the message queue.** Messages awaiting timing decisions sit in SQS with visibility timeouts aligned to their delivery windows. SQS handles the durability, ordering, and retry semantics. Configure a dead letter queue (DLQ) on the main queue with a `maxReceiveCount` of 3. Messages that fail timing decision processing after 3 attempts land in the DLQ for manual investigation rather than cycling indefinitely. Set the visibility timeout to at least 60 seconds (enough time for the Lambda to fetch patient context, call Personalize, and confirm schedule creation before the message becomes visible again).
