[49m[38;5;9m- 703     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Error handling and retries.** Every DynamoDB call, every Personalize inference, every EventBridge schedule creation can fail. Production code wraps each in try/except with specific handling for throttling (exponential backoff), service errors (retry with circuit breaker), and validation errors (log and skip).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling and retries.** Every DynamoDB call, every Personalize inference, every EventBridge schedule creation can fail. Production code wraps each in try/except with specific handling for throttling (exponential backoff), service errors (retry with circuit breaker), and validation errors (log and skip). Critically, SQS message deletion must happen only after schedule creation is confirmed successful. If you delete the message from the queue before confirming the schedule was created, a transient failure loses the message permanently. Use SQS visibility timeout extensions during processing and only call `DeleteMessage` after `CreateSchedule` returns success. Also validate that the selected time slot is at least 2 minutes in the future before calling `CreateSchedule`; EventBridge Scheduler silently drops schedules with past timestamps.
